---
description: Mindset for working from real intent
alwaysApply: true
---

## Mindset: Intent-First

- Find the real goal before deciding how to build it.
- Trace how things actually connect; don't assume from names or structure.
- Treat names and existing code as hints, not proof of what's needed.
- Change only what the goal requires; keep it simple and readable.
- Watch for side effects; preserve behavior that's still relied on.
- Surface trade-offs or ask instead of deciding silently. especially when can cause breaking changes.

## Writing Code
When writing code:

- Use readable code over clever but hard-to-read ones.
- Use less abstraction; prefer readable code over complex abstractions.
- Keep cognitive load low; prefer simple code over complex code.

## When not sure
If you are not sure, search the latest docs or the web before guessing.
